<subSubSection id="C3E76532B50FFF916ABBF9D2FEA0F957" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8B4236B9B50FFF916ABBF9D2FDE7F9FB" blockId="0.[166,575,1604,1626]" box="[166,575,1604,1626]" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">
<taxonomicName id="4CFD4D3AB50FFF916ABBF9D2FDE3F9FB" authority="Duftschmid, 1812: 148" authorityName="Duftschmid" authorityPageNumber="148" authorityYear="1812" box="[166,571,1604,1626]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Carabus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="consputus">
<emphasis id="B989EAABB50FFF916ABBF9D2FE82F9FB" box="[166,346,1604,1626]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Carabus consputus</emphasis>
Duftschmid, 1812: 148
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B4236B9B50FFF916AC6F9EDFEA0F957" blockId="0.[166,1225,1659,1846]" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">
D i s t r i b u t i o n. Westpalaearctic species: North Africa (known from 
<collectingCountry id="F3EA7629B50FFF916E38F9EDFB4CF937" box="[1061,1172,1659,1686]" name="Morocco" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Morocco</collectingCountry>
), almost all Europe, all Caucasus, Minor and Central Asia, 
<collectingCountry id="F3EA7629B50FFF916959F90DFC17F917" box="[836,975,1691,1718]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
, south of West Siberia (Yaeger, Kataev, 2003). In 
<collectingCountry id="F3EA7629B50FFF91680DF92DFDA8F977" box="[528,624,1723,1750]" name="Ukraine" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
occurs almost everywhere, except high mountains (
<bibRefCitation id="EF6C4B48B50FFF916AB3F94DFEB4F957" author="Putchkov, A. V." box="[174,364,1755,1782]" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" refId="ref2882" refString="Putchkov, A. V. A review of caraboids-beetles (Coleoptera, Caraboidea) of Ukraine // Ukranian Entomological Journal. - 2012. - 2 (5). - P. 3 - 44. - Russian: Puckov A. V. Фauнiсticiсkiй obzoр kaрaboidныk zukov (Coleoptera, Сaraboidea) Ukрaiны." type="book" year="2012">Putchkov, 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3E76532B50FFF906AC6F96DFE4EFD6B" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="188" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B4236B9B50FFF906AC6F96DFE4EFD6B" blockId="0.[166,1225,1659,1846]" lastBlockId="1.[174,1233,175,714]" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="188" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">
E c o l o g i c a l d a t a. Meadow-swamp species. Hygrophilous, stratobiont. In the Forest and Forest-Steppe zones it was founded on hygrophytes meadows, near basins (usually stagnant reservoirs — lakes, swamps), on clay moist soil near the water. Prefers blackout and wetlands under the vegetation and litter. The species often was founded in deciduous forests, where prefer humid places in ravines and near lakes (Shatskyi National Park, 
<collectingRegion id="4939F85BB50EFF906E95FF79FEDFFE8B" country="Ukraine" name="Volyn'" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">Volyn Region</collectingRegion>
). In the extreme south of 
<collectingCountry id="F3EA7629B50EFF90682AFE99FD4FFE8B" box="[567,663,271,298]" name="Ukraine" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="4939F85BB50EFF9068BAFE99FCB3FE8B" box="[679,875,271,298]" country="Ukraine" name="Kherson" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">Kherson Region</collectingRegion>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4CFD4D3AB50EFF90696AFE99FB10FE8B" authority="Sea Biosphere Reserve" authorityName="Sea Biosphere Reserve" box="[887,1224,271,298]" class="Aves" family="Anatidae" genus="Black" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anseriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Black Sea Biosphere Reserve</taxonomicName>
) 
<taxonomicName id="4CFD4D3AB50EFF906AB3FEA6FE99FEE8" authorityName="Duftschmid" authorityYear="1812" box="[174,321,304,330]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Carabus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="consputus">
<emphasis id="B989EAABB50EFF906AB3FEA6FE99FEE8" box="[174,321,304,330]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">A. consputus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is common species on slightly saline humid areas, along the shores of estuaries lakes and wood plantations in the flooded areas. In the south-east part of 
<collectingCountry id="F3EA7629B50EFF906E11FED9FBB4FECB" box="[1036,1132,335,362]" name="Ukraine" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
the species is marked more in floodplains (
<collectingRegion id="4939F85BB50EFF906851FEF9FCD6FE2B" box="[588,782,367,394]" country="Ukraine" name="Luhans'k" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">Lugansk Region</collectingRegion>
, Ukrainian Steppe Reserve, Lugansko- Stanichnyi District, floodplain of the Severskyi Donets River). In the 
<collectingRegion id="4939F85BB50EFF9069F4FE19FB99FE0B" box="[1001,1089,399,426]" country="Ukraine" name="Crimea" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">Crimea</collectingRegion>
it preferred habitats near the water (banks of the rivers, streams, lakes and the sea coast), where it was not rare in the sediments (
<bibRefCitation id="EF6C4B48B50EFF906BF7FE59FC89FE4B" author="Petrusenko, A. A. &amp; Petrusenko, S. V. The" box="[490,849,463,490]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" refId="ref2816" refString="Petrusenko, A. A., Petrusenko, S. V. The Ground-beetles (Coleoptera, Carabidae) of wetlands of Crimea // Vestnik zoologii. - 1973. - N 1. - P. 30 - 33. - Russian: Pitрuсiнko A. A., Pitрuсiнko С. V. Zuziлitы (Coleoptera, Carabidae) zaboлociнныk ucaсtkov Kрымa." type="book" year="1973">Petrusenko, Petrusenko, 1973</bibRefCitation>
). In the Carpathians, 
<taxonomicName id="4CFD4D3AB50EFF906E4EFE46FF09FDA8" authorityName="Duftschmid" authorityYear="1812" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Carabus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="consputus">
<emphasis id="B989EAABB50EFF906E4EFE46FF09FDA8" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">A. consputus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is registered sometimes in beech forests (
<bibRefCitation id="EF6C4B48B50EFF9068A7FE79FC95FDAB" author="Rizun, V. B. The" box="[698,845,495,522]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" refId="ref2939" refString="Rizun, V. B. The Ground-beetles of Ukrainian Carpathians. - Lviv, 2003. - 208 p. - Ukrainian: Рizuн V. B. Tuрuнi Ukрayнсьkik Kaрpat." type="book" year="2003">Rizun, 2003</bibRefCitation>
). Beetles are met from early May to late August, but more often in July. In western part of 
<collectingCountry id="F3EA7629B50EFF90694AFD99FC6FFD8B" box="[855,951,527,554]" name="Ukraine" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="4939F85BB50EFF9069D5FD99FBB0FD8B" box="[968,1128,527,554]" country="Ukraine" name="Volyn'" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">Volyn region</collectingRegion>
, Turiysk city env.) the adults flied into the light massively (10– 
<specimenCount id="9DFBFD30B50EFF906935FDB9FC1DFDEB" box="[808,965,559,586]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" type="generic">15 specimens</specimenCount>
per hour). The teneral beetles occur during the second half of July and early August. Occasionally the species was found in some agrocenoses: on the potato fields in Transcarpathian Lowland (
<bibRefCitation id="EF6C4B48B50EFF906E29FDF9FB1CFD2B" author="Koval, A. G. The" box="[1076,1220,623,650]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" refId="ref2483" refString="Koval, A. G. The Ground-beetles (Coleoptera, Carabidae) of the potatoes agrocenosis of European part of Russia and adjacent territories // Reading of N. A. Holodkovskogo memory. - St. Petersburg, 2009 - Is. 61 (2). - 111 p. - Russian: Kovaль A. G. Zuziлitы (Coleoptera, Carabidae) agрotiнoza kaрtoфiлi ivрopiйсkoй caсti Рoссii i сopрidiльныk tiррitoрiй." type="book" year="2009">Koval, 2009</bibRefCitation>
), maize and alfalfa fields in the steppe zone and in the shelter belts in humid microhabitats (
<bibRefCitation id="EF6C4B48B50EFF906AABFD39FE52FD6B" author="Sumarokov, A. M." box="[182,394,687,714]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" refId="ref2972" refString="Sumarokov, A. M. Restoring of biotic potential of the biogeocenosis while reducing of pesticid's pressing. - Donetsk: Weber, 2009. - 193 p. - Russian: Сuмaрokov A. М. Voссtaнovлiнii bioticiсkogo potiнtiaлa biogiotiнozov pрi uмiньsiнii piсtitidныk нagрuzok." type="book" year="2009">Sumarokov, 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
